    <fr:title text="Birkhoff’s representation theorem for distributive lattices">Birkhoff’s representation theorem for distributive lattices</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>The category of finite posets and monotone maps is anti-equivalent to the category of finite distributive lattices: a finite poset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is sent to the finite distributive lattice <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [P,{\mathopen {}\left  [1\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> of (decidable) downsets.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
